"content": "<h2>Barns were associated with industry and prosperity</h2>\n<h3>Full barns were a sign of blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:9-Prov3:10\">PRO 3:9–3:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:8\">DEU 28:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:12-Ps144:15\">PSA 144:12–144:15</a></p>\n<h3>Empty barns were a sign of poverty</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:15-Hag2:19\">HAG 2:15–2:19</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The priority of spiritual over material prosperity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:15-Luke12:21\">LUK 12:15–12:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:25-Matt6:26\">MAT 6:25–6:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:23-Luke12:24\">LUK 12:23–12:24</a></p>\n<h2>God's barn is a metaphor for the kingdom of heaven</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:16-Luke3:17\">LUK 3:16–3:17</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:11-Matt3:12\">MAT 3:11–3:12</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:24-Matt13:30\">MAT 13:24–13:30</a></p>",
